Dear students,
In this module you learned the basics of programming and internalized core principles using the Python programming language.
During this module you learned the following topics:
Pseudo Code


Introduction to computational (programming) thinking


Introduction to programming


Variables and data structures


Using conditions


Using loops


Using functions


Using advanced libraries such as Socket, OS, Requests, Scapy, and more


This knowledge will be essential for you later in the course, as you will be required to identify and understand how code works in order to demonstrate your knowledge to your instructor.
The submission deadline is two weeks from the date of receipt.
 You are required to submit one exercise only, of your choice.
 There are five exercises in total, presented to you.
Please note:
The solution must be written according to the required behavior.


You must follow this instruction sheet (unless your instructor instructs otherwise).


This project includes, as part of its completion, internet research on additional material, so that you can practice your online research skills.


The project is submitted in groups, and in addition to the code, you are required to explain each line of the code.


The purpose of this assignment is for you to understand what you are doing and not just copy code. Although most of the challenges can be almost fully solved using information from the internet, you must demonstrate understanding.


You must also provide a general explanation of the process.


Project submission must be in a Word file, which includes:
Explanations of the code


The participants


A general explanation of the programming process


The code itself


